column6: How aware were you of the real world surrounding while navigating in the virtual world? (i.e. sounds, room temperature, other people, etc.)?
column7: How real did the virtual world seem to you?
column8: How much did your experience in the virtual environment seem consistent with your real world experience ?
column9: I felt present in the virtual space.
column10: In the computer generated world I had a sense of "being there".
column11: I felt as if the virtual arm moved just like I wanted it to, as if it was obeying my will.

column13: I felt that the interaction with the environment was realistic.
column14: I felt like I controlled the virtual arm.

column16: I felt as if the virtual arm was someone else’s.

column18: To what extent did you feel able to assess your opponents’ reactions?
